(json 1 (id 35))
(json 1 (name "Community RFPs"))
(json 1 (slug "community-rfp"))
(json 1 (max_funding_amount "120,000"))
(json 1 (description "Request for proposals (RFPs) offer a targeted way to define desired project proposals. By making RFPs we are -to some extent- seperating the definition process from the development process.

In this pool you can select an RFP and create a proposal for that RFP.
Important:
- Each RFP has very specific requirements and each proposal has to comply with all 'must have' requirements of the RFP.
- The DF team will filter out proposals that do not comply to these requirements and, reserves the right to subjectively reject proposals/teams that offer low confidence in their capability to deliver.

Before preparing a proposal, ensure that you have carefully read the full text and conditions of the RFP. You can find all active RFP's on https://deepfunding.ai/all-rfps"))
